Session close — P1, world_005_marrick. We converged, so I'll bank what we jointly nailed down and leave the rest on the cutting-room floor.

The through-line of this session isn't the grip — the grip was never in question. It's that a clean-holding line can hide a stall by letting the *same* failure re-enter under new nouns, and that you were judging each turn on its own merits (correctly) in a way that structurally cannot surface a recurrence which only exists in the diff between T17 and T40. You named the fix yourself: a live binary annotation per learner turn, and a two-consecutive-same-frame trip to the counterfactual. That's bankable because it's countable, and we verified it doesn't false-positive on T14.

Three notes, then one patch to the (blank) book's Technique section.

